// Purpose:
- Clarify the Problem: Identify the specific problem or need that your search engine aims to address.
- Target Audience: Determine the primary users or audience for your search engine.
- Use Cases: List the different use cases your search engine will serve.
- Unique Selling Proposition (USP): Define what will make your search engine stand out from competitors.

// Scope:
- Data Sources: Specify the types of data sources your search engine will access.
- Content Types: Identify the types of content your search engine will index and search through.
- Languages: Determine the languages your search engine will support.
- Geographic Coverage: Decide whether your search engine will have regional or global coverage.
- Platform and Devices: Specify the platforms and devices your search engine will support.
- Monetization Model: If applicable, define how you plan to monetize your search engine.
- Timeframe: Set a timeline for the development and launch of the search engine.
- Regulatory Considerations: Be aware of any legal or regulatory constraints that may affect the scope of your project.
